provided by well-known scholars in diverse fields, with a smaller number of internal perspectives provided by prominent ELF scholars, it will be of interest not only to students and researchers interested in ELF, but also to students and scholars in Applied Linguistics, Sociolinguistics and Intercultural Communication.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCross-cultural orientation. 0aEnglish languagexInfluence on foreign languages. 0aEnglish languagexVariation. 0aInterrcultural communication. 0aLanguage and culture. 0aLanguage and education. 0aLanguages in contact. 0aLingua francas. 4aLingua Franca. 4aPerspektivität. 4aSprachwissenschaftler. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aELF.  aEnglish as a Lingua Franca.  aEnglish.1 aBianco, Joseph Lo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBjörkman, Beyza, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrutt-Griffler, Janina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCogo, Alessia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCook, Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDalton-Puffer, Christiane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuido, Maria Grazia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHouse, Juliane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHua, Zhu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHülmbauer, Cornelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJenkins, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaur, Jagdish, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKe